The Poltergeist.description:
}}

Nobody knows what it truly is, but the Poltergeist has no need to answer why, how or where it exists. That is too irrelevant. The Poltergeist is bored. It wants a game to play. But what game is there to play in the Backrooms? At least, one that is fun and doesn't result in your immediate death? Well, none really, but one can always improvise.

That is what the Poltergeist thinks.

The Poltergeist isn't a physical entity, it is a... psychological entity. While not solid or bound to a strict form, it is created out of the collective curiosity, wonder, and sense of mystery shared by all wanderers of the Backrooms. And thus, depending on the intensity of these emotions, the Poltergeist can be calm, hostile, benevolent, and many other infinite possibilities.

However, one trait is consistent. It is bored. It wants to play and satisfy this boredom by any means possible. The Poltergeist is a deity, however. It acts like a hivemind; however, each lifeform has their own version of the Poltergeist. And while the type of Poltergeist they have is defined ever since birth, even before entering the Backrooms, it doesn't mean the Poltergeist is subject to changing behaviors over time.

