The Great Wall Of REDACTED.description:
The Great Wall Of [REDACTED], also known and mentioned as "The Wall" and "The Watcher", is a dangerous entity with unimaginable power and knowledge of things such as important events that date back to before the existence of the universe. The first existing records of the existence of The Great Wall Of [REDACTED] date back to 2300 BC, as multiple unearthed carvings on the walls of caves that reference the wall date back to that epoch. A theory states that following the creation of the universe, The Great Wall Of [REDACTED] had been corrupted by an unknown substance that appeared alongside the universe according to certain discovered notes (one of which, has been pasted above). Although a formal name for the substance hasn't been decided upon, the officials that are currently investigating the entity referred to the strange material as [REDACTED] for the time being, thus creating its name. Since the project of investigation is still in its very early stages, the information thus gathered must be taken with a grain of salt, as there is no reliable way yet to confirm or deny the investigation team's findings.

The entity's appearance is exceptionally strange. It resembles a gigantic wall of unknown measurements with an enormous eye at its core. It's made out of a substance that officials currently call [REDACTED], as no attempt to identify the substance has proven successful. The eye on the wall is its only known weakness. If a wanderer manages to stab or otherwise damage the eye, the entity would fade away, dying. However, the wall has defensive measures of its own. The corpses of the wanderers who have tried killing the entity can be seen stretching from the wall, seemingly alive. However, they are not. The wall has the power to reanimate corpses for them to do their bidding. Most corpses will use their "hands" to latch onto the wanderer, which then they will rip apart limb from limb. However, some corpses are armed with weapons such as knives and will attack whoever tries to approach the entity. Much like the entity, the corpses have also been covered in the substance [REDACTED].

Although it's possible to defeat this entity, it is strongly advised not to underestimate its abilities, as some of its abilities can defy the laws of physics. The entity can only travel through Boundaries and not regular levels. Its abilities include wrecking areas, turning everything upside down, and even using the corpses that it controls to break through walls. It can also suck a person's soul, leaving them to roam around mindlessly. It can also expand or shrink at will, but the entity very rarely uses this ability, only using it when endangered. It can also quickly regenerate and even grow limbs by using the strange substance it is covered in.

The entity has the ability to speak, however, the way it communicates is very odd. It can somehow speak without a mouth and only speaks in gibberish. However, its "words" are linked, and it communicates by using only the first letter of the words it invented (ex. should the entity say "tsajd hrj elwq", it means "the".) However, after its way of communication was deciphered it refuses to speak to regular human beings and instead only talks to other powerful entities.

There is a being capable of manipulating space and time. Capable of defeating even the most powerful entities in the Backrooms. This being does not have a name, it is only referred to as It. This being has incomprehensible power and strength, it has the ability to break the space-time continuum in such a way that it can no longer be repaired. It's speculated that It resides in The Other Side. Most information about this entity is as clear as mud. The information written here is not fully guaranteed_

"Greetings, from the Voidpeople. You are reaching the end of your story. We will be watching you."
